HEADWORD: Enorthotrope
<hw>En*or"tho*trope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ in +
<?/ upright, correct + <?/ to turn.]</ety> <def>An optical toy; a card
on which confused or imperfect figures are drawn, but which form to the
eye regular figures when the card is rapidly revolved. See
<er>Thaumatrope</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

